						               													<description>A new scenario for Battle for Greyport.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Scenario comes from The Red Dragon Inn: Battle for Greyport: Store Event Kits &amp;ndash; Season 2&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This scenario comes in two flavours of difficulty so both introductory and seasoned players should find a good time.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Look Out Below! (For new players)&amp;#10;- Use the &amp;quot;Torglesnarf Returns&amp;quot; scenario from the game, with the following changes:&amp;#10;- Encounter 1: Each player's monster group starts with a Kite Bomber whose threat counts toward that player's total. Location monsters are set up normally.&amp;#10;- Encounter 2: After setup, each player adds a Gnome Gunner to their hand and a Kite Bomber to their monster group.&amp;#10;- Enounter 3:Use the Dragon's Fist instead of The Blackened Kraken. If the Dragon's Fist is destroyed, Captain Blake becomes active and loses his armor for the rest of the game. After setup, each player adds a Kite Bomber to their monster group.&amp;#10;- Recommended rest healing: 2&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Look Out Below! (Advanced players)&amp;#10;- Use the &amp;quot;Torglesnarf Returns&amp;quot; scenario from the game, with the following changes:&amp;#10;- Encounter 1: Each player's monster group starts with a Kite Bomber whose threat counts toward that player's total. Location monsters are set up normally.&amp;#10;- Encounter 2: After setup, each player adds a Gnome Gunner to the top of their deck and a Kite Bomber to their monster group.&amp;#10;- Enounter 3:Use the Viceroy Lapentius and the Dragon's Fist instead of Cpatain Blake and The Blackened Kraken. After setup, each player adds a Kite Bomber to their monster group.&amp;#10;- Recommended rest healing: 1&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
